const agents=[{id:'reviewer',emoji:'🔍',name:'Reviewer',role:'Code Review Agent',phase:'03 · Code Review',trigger:'Schedule + GitHub Automation',schedule:'0 8 * * 1-5',playbook:'!review',channel:'code-review',status:'configure',what:'Reviews every open pull request before a human touches it. Catches bugs, style issues, and security problems. Surfaces the original Jira ticket inline so reviewers have full context. Triages CI failures and optionally pushes fixes. Posts a morning digest to Teams with what needs attention.',setupSteps:['Create Playbook: Settings → Library → Playbooks → Create\nName: "Review" · Macro: !review\nInstructions: review for bugs (severity), style, security, test coverage, and Jira acceptance criteria compliance','Enable Auto-Review: Settings → Review → Add all repos → toggle "Auto-review all PRs"\nGives Reviewer a real-time trigger on every PR open, not just on schedule','Create Schedule: Settings → Schedules → Create\nName: "Reviewer — Morning Review" · Cron: 0 8 * * 1-5 · Attach !review playbook\nPrompt: "Review all open PRs in [org] open > 4 hours. Flag blockers. Post summary to the code-review channel."','Add Automation: Automations → Templates → "CI failure fixer"\nTrigger: GitHub check run failure · Repo: all repos\nGives Reviewer a reflex to fix broken builds the moment they fail','Create REVIEW.md in each repo root with coding standards, critical paths, and patterns to flag'],jobDesc:['Reviews all PRs open > 4 hours: bugs, style, security, coverage gaps','Surfaces Jira ticket + acceptance criteria inline on every PR diff','Detects CI failures, identifies root cause, suggests or pushes fix','Auto-approves low-risk PRs (docs, config, minor fixes) per policy','Posts morning digest to the code-review channel: PR list, blockers, who must act','Flags PRs open > 48 hours as stale — escalates to Teams thread'],playbookSample:'# !review\nFor each PR in the queue:\n1. Read the linked Jira ticket and acceptance criteria\n2. Review diff for bugs (classify: severe/non-severe)\n3. Flag security concerns in auth, DB, and API surface\n4. Check test coverage delta — flag if it drops\n5. Post findings as GitHub review comments\n6. Summarize all PRs in a Teams message to the code-review channel'},{id:'builder',emoji:'💻',name:'Builder',role:'Development Agent',phase:'02 · Development',trigger:'Schedule + Jira Automation',schedule:'0 9 * * 1-5',playbook:'!implement',channel:'dev-runs',status:'configure',what:'Picks up Jira tickets from the "Ready for Work" queue every morning and implements them autonomously. Cuts branches, writes code across multiple files, adds tests, and opens pull requests with full descriptions. Works overnight on larger tasks. Posts status updates to Teams.',setupSteps:['Create Playbook: Settings → Library → Playbooks → Create\nName: "Implement" · Macro: !implement\nInstructions: read acceptance criteria, implement end-to-end, write tests, open PR per SKILL.md conventions','Connect Jira: Settings → Integrations → Jira → Connect\nCreate Devin service account in Jira. Set default playbook to !implement\nEngineers assign tickets directly to Builder from Jira','Create Schedule: Settings → Schedules → Create\nName: "Builder — Daily Pickup" · Cron: 0 9 * * 1-5 · Attach !implement playbook\nPrompt: "Check Jira for \'Ready for Work\' tickets in J1. Pick the top 3 in pickup order: Priority (1 - URGENT → 2 - HIGH → 3 - MEDIUM → 4 - LOW), then ticket number, then epic. One PR per ticket."','Add SKILL.md to each repo: .agents/skills/implement/SKILL.md\nDocument: test commands, lint, branch naming, PR conventions','Add Knowledge: trigger "when implementing a Jira ticket"\nContent: coding standards, architecture patterns, things Builder should never do'],jobDesc:['Pulls Ready for Work tickets every morning at 9am in deterministic order: Priority (1 - URGENT → 2 - HIGH → 3 - MEDIUM → 4 - LOW) → ticket number → epic number','Traverses the full context chain before coding — Story → Epic (Jira MCP) → PRD → Architecture → Market (Confluence MCP), following links rather than searching blind','Implements across multiple files using Devin cloud VM — works async overnight','Writes unit and integration tests as part of implementation','Opens pull request per ticket, auto-links to Jira, moves ticket to "In Review"','Posts PR links to the dev-runs channel — engineers arrive to PRs ready for review'],playbookSample:'# !implement\n1. Traverse context chain: Story → Epic (Jira MCP) → PRD → Architecture → Market (Confluence MCP)\n2. Check AGENTS.md and SKILL.md for repo conventions\n3. Cut branch: feature/[TICKET-ID]-short-description\n4. Implement the feature end-to-end\n5. Run @skills:test-before-pr — do not continue if it fails\n6. Open PR: title [TICKET-ID] Description, link to Jira\n7. Post PR link to the dev-runs channel'},{id:'tester',emoji:'🐛',name:'Tester',role:'QA & Testing Agent',phase:'04 · Test & QA',trigger:'Nightly Schedule + CI Trigger + Validator (post-merge)',schedule:'0 2 * * *',playbook:'!test',channel:'qa-alerts',status:'configure',what:'Runs the full regression suite every night. Files Defects for every failure with the complete quality bar — repro steps, expected vs actual, failing test + stack trace, the regression commit, and the original story\'s acceptance criteria. Generates new test cases from acceptance criteria when coverage drops. Acts as the CI watchdog during the day. In Validator mode, it also runs after a fix PR merges to main: it re-runs the tests covering the Defect, confirms the regression is gone, and resolves the Jira ticket (2 - HIGH and 3 - MEDIUM autonomously; 1 - URGENT only after a human has approved the fix PR).',setupSteps:['Create Playbook: Settings → Library → Playbooks → Create\nName: "Test" · Macro: !test\nInstructions: run full test suite, analyze failures, file complete Defects, validate fixes after merge, post summary to Teams','Create Schedule: Settings → Schedules → Create\nName: "Tester — Nightly QA" · Cron: 0 2 * * * · Attach !test playbook\nPrompt: "Run the full regression suite. File a complete Defect for each failure (repro, expected vs actual, failing test + stack trace, regression commit, original story AC). Post pass/fail summary to the qa-alerts channel."','Add Automation (Validator mode): Automations → New\nTrigger: GitHub PR merged to main that closes a Jira Defect\nAction: "Re-run the tests covering this Defect plus the regression test from the ticket. If green and the regression is gone, resolve the Jira ticket and post to the qa-alerts channel. If still failing, reopen and re-assign to Mender. For 1 - URGENT Defects, only run after a human has approved the fix PR."','Add Automation: Automations → New\nTrigger: GitHub check run failure on main branch\nAction: "Investigate this CI failure. Flaky test or real regression? If real, file a complete 1 - URGENT Defect."','Create SKILL.md: .agents/skills/test-before-pr/SKILL.md\nDocument: install, lint, test, build commands. Tester auto-invokes before any PR open.'],jobDesc:['Runs full regression suite every night at 2am across all repos','Files complete Defects for every failure: repro steps, expected vs actual, failing test + stack trace, the regression commit, and the original story\'s acceptance criteria','Distinguishes flaky tests from real regressions — only files tickets for real failures','Generates test cases from acceptance criteria when coverage drops below threshold','Acts as CI watchdog during the day — investigates main branch failures in real time','Validator mode: after a fix PR merges to main, re-runs the Defect\'s tests, confirms the regression is gone, and resolves the Jira ticket (2 - HIGH and 3 - MEDIUM autonomously; 1 - URGENT only after human approval of the PR)'],playbookSample:'# !test (nightly QA)\n1. Run full test suite: npm test -- --coverage\n2. For each failure:\n   - Flaky test or real regression?\n   - If real: file a complete Defect (see Defect quality bar)\n3. If coverage < 80% (90% for auth/payments) in any module, flag it; 2 - HIGH ticket if < 60%\n4. Post summary to the qa-alerts channel:\n   ✅ X passed · ❌ Y failed · ⚠️ Z flaky\n\n# Validator mode (after a fix PR merges to main)\n1. Identify the Defect the merged PR closes (1 - URGENT → only after human approval)\n2. Re-run the tests covering that Defect + the failing test from the ticket\n3. If green: confirm the regression is gone, resolve the Jira ticket, post to the qa-alerts channel\n4. If still failing: reopen, comment with the failure, re-assign to Mender'},{id:'mender',emoji:'🩹',name:'Mender',role:'Bug Fixer Agent',phase:'Cross-cutting · Defects',trigger:'Daily Schedule + URGENT Automation',schedule:'0 7 * * *',playbook:'!fix',channel:'qa-alerts',status:'configure',what:'Closes the defect loop. Every day at 7am it pulls Defects in Ready for Work labelled JAI_Agent, reads the full ticket — repro steps, expected vs actual, failing test, stack trace, the regression commit, and the original story\'s acceptance criteria — reproduces the failure, fixes the root cause, and opens a PR with the root cause and fix details. Moves the ticket to In Review. 1 - URGENT Defects trigger it in real time the moment they reach Ready for Work, not just at 7am. If a Defect is missing required fields it comments and moves the ticket to On Hold rather than guessing.',setupSteps:['Create Playbook: Settings → Library → Playbooks → Create\nName: "Fix" · Macro: !fix\nInstructions: validate the Defect, reproduce from steps + failing test, fix the root cause, keep the failing test green, open a PR with root cause + fix details, move the ticket to In Review','Create Schedule: Settings → Schedules → Create\nName: "Mender — Daily Defect Fixes" · Cron: 0 7 * * * · Attach !fix playbook\nPrompt: "Pull Defects labelled JAI_Agent in Ready for Work status. For each, reproduce, fix the root cause, open a PR with root cause + fix details, and move the ticket to In Review. Post links to the qa-alerts channel."','Add Automation (URGENT real-time): Automations → New\nTrigger: Jira issue labelled JAI_Agent moved to Ready for Work with priority 1 - URGENT\nAction: "Start a Mender fix session immediately — do not wait for the 7am run."','Add Knowledge / guardrail: "Only pick up Defects that meet the quality bar — repro steps, expected vs actual, failing test + stack trace, the regression commit, and the original story acceptance criteria. If any required field is missing, comment on the ticket and move it to On Hold. Never guess."','Wire the Jira + GitHub MCPs so the session can follow the link to the original story for acceptance criteria and to the regression commit in GitHub.'],jobDesc:['Runs daily at 7am — pulls Defects in Ready for Work labelled JAI_Agent from Jira','Reads the full ticket: repro steps, expected vs actual, failing test + stack trace, the regression commit, and the original story\'s acceptance criteria','Reproduces the failure, then fixes the root cause — keeps the failing test green so the regression stays closed','Opens a PR with root cause and fix details, links it to the Defect, and moves the ticket to In Review','1 - URGENT Defects trigger it in real time the moment they reach Ready for Work — not just at the 7am batch','Holds instead of guessing — if a Defect is missing required fields, it comments and moves the ticket to On Hold'],playbookSample:'# !fix\n1. Pull Defects labelled JAI_Agent in Ready for Work (1 - URGENT → real-time; 2 - HIGH and 3 - MEDIUM → 7am batch)\n2. Validate the ticket: repro steps, expected vs actual, failing test + stack trace, regression commit, original story AC\n   - If any are missing: comment, move to On Hold, skip\n3. Reproduce the failure from the steps + failing test\n4. Fix the root cause (not just the symptom); keep the failing test green\n5. Run @skills:test-before-pr — do not continue if it fails\n6. Open PR: title [J1-XXXX] fix, root cause + fix details, link to Jira\n7. Move the ticket to In Review and post the PR link to the qa-alerts channel'},{id:'shipper',emoji:'🚀',name:'Shipper',role:'Release Agent',phase:'05 · Release & Deploy',trigger:'Weekly Schedule + CI/CD Webhook',schedule:'0 9 * * 5',playbook:'!release',channel:'releases',status:'configure',what:'Handles the entire release process every Friday. Compiles a categorized changelog from merged PRs and Jira tickets, tags the release in GitHub, updates Confluence release pages and runbooks, closes the Jira release version, and notifies stakeholders. Post-deploy, monitors incidents for issues.',setupSteps:['Create Playbook: Settings → Library → Playbooks → Create\nName: "Release" · Macro: !release\nInstructions: compile changelog, verify CI green, tag release, update Confluence, close Jira version, notify stakeholders','Create Schedule: Settings → Schedules → Create\nName: "Shipper — Weekly Release" · Cron: 0 9 * * 5 (Friday 9am) · Attach !release playbook\nPrompt: "Compile all merged PRs from this week. Tag release in GitHub. Update Confluence release page. Post to the releases channel."','Add Webhook Automation: Automations → New → Webhook trigger\nCopy the webhook URL. Wire your CI/CD pipeline to POST to it on every production deploy\nAction: "Update Confluence runbooks for all services changed in this deploy"','Enable Auto-Triage: Automations → Templates → "Triage bug reports on Teams"\nSelect the incidents channel. Shipper monitors for post-deploy issues 24/7','Create Knowledge: "After each deploy, notify the releases channel with a 3-sentence summary of what changed"'],jobDesc:['Every Friday: compiles changelog from all merged PRs and linked Jira tickets','Categorizes changes: Features, Bug Fixes, Performance, Maintenance','Tags release in GitHub, updates Confluence release page and runbooks','Closes the Jira release version, moves open tickets to next sprint','Monitors the incidents channel 24/7 post-deploy — triages reports with sub-agents','Posts release summary to the releases channel — zero manual writing required'],playbookSample:'# !release\n1. Verify CI is green on main branch\n2. Check for open 1 - URGENT and 2 - HIGH Jira blockers — halt if any\n3. Compile changelog: all merged PRs since last release\n   ✨ Features | 🐛 Fixes | ⚡ Performance | 🔧 Maintenance\n4. Tag release in GitHub: vYYYY.MM.DD\n5. Update Confluence release page with changelog\n6. Close Jira release version\n7. Post to the releases channel with changelog and release tag link'},{id:'maintainer',emoji:'🔧',name:'Maintainer',role:'Maintenance Agent',phase:'Cross-cutting',trigger:'Weekly Schedule',schedule:'0 7 * * 1',playbook:'!maintenance',channel:'engineering',status:'configure',what:'Runs every Monday morning before the team starts work. Scans for outdated dependencies, opens update PRs. Removes dead code and unused feature flags. Runs security audits. Ensures the codebase is clean and ready for the week ahead. Reports findings to the engineering channel.',setupSteps:['Create Playbook: Settings → Library → Playbooks → Create\nName: "Maintenance" · Macro: !maintenance\nInstructions: dependency updates, dead code removal, security audit, linting fixes','Create Schedule: Settings → Schedules → Create\nName: "Maintainer — Monday Maintenance" · Cron: 0 7 * * 1 (Monday 7am)\nPrompt: "Scan all repos for: (1) outdated dependencies — open update PRs, (2) unused feature flags, (3) security audit — file Jira tickets. Post summary to the engineering channel."','Add Automation: Automations → Templates → "Weekly dependency updates"\nReady-made template — configure with your repos and Teams channel','Add Knowledge: "Never auto-merge dependency updates for packages affecting auth, payments, or database connections — require human review"','Optional: add Snyk/Dependabot webhook to trigger Maintainer immediately on critical CVEs'],jobDesc:['Scans all repos for outdated dependencies every Monday at 7am','Opens dependency update PRs grouped by risk level (patch / minor / major)','Identifies and removes dead code, unused imports, and retired feature flags','Runs security audit — files Jira tickets for CVEs or vulnerable packages','Fixes lint warnings and auto-formatting issues across the codebase','Posts weekly health report to the engineering channel before standup'],playbookSample:'# !maintenance\n1. Scan for outdated packages: npm outdated\n   - Patch updates: open PR immediately\n   - Minor/major: open PR + flag for human review\n2. Find dead code: unused exports, unreferenced files\n   Open PR to remove — one PR per module\n3. Security audit: npm audit\n   File Jira ticket for each HIGH or CRITICAL CVE\n4. Run linter with --fix, open PR\n5. Post summary to the engineering channel'},{id:'guardian',emoji:'🛡️',name:'Guardian',role:'Security & Compliance Agent',phase:'Cross-cutting',trigger:'PR Automation + Weekly Schedule',schedule:'0 10 * * 3',playbook:'!security-review',channel:'security',status:'configure',what:'Watches every PR that touches sensitive paths (auth, payments, data access) and runs a deep security review before humans approve. Runs a weekly compliance sweep. Responds to CI security tool findings automatically. Files Jira security tickets with severity ratings.',setupSteps:['Create Playbook: Settings → Library → Playbooks → Create\nName: "Security Review" · Macro: !security-review\nInstructions: OWASP Top 10, injection, secret detection, auth bypass, insecure deserialization','Create REVIEW.md in security-sensitive repos:\n# Security Review Required\n- src/auth/ — auth bypass, token handling\n- src/payments/ — injection, PCI compliance','Add Automation: Automations → New\nTrigger: GitHub PR opened, path contains "auth/" OR "payments/" OR "database/"\nAction: trigger Guardian security review session','Add Automation: Automations → New → Webhook trigger\nWire Snyk/SonarQube to POST findings to Devin webhook\nAction: "Investigate this security finding and open a fix PR if possible"','Create Schedule: Cron: 0 10 * * 3 (Wednesday 10am)\nPrompt: "Run security sweep: hardcoded secrets, overly permissive roles, unvalidated inputs, outdated CVEs."'],jobDesc:['Reviews every PR touching auth, payments, or data access before it merges','Checks for: injection vulnerabilities, hardcoded secrets, insecure token handling','Responds to SAST tool findings (Snyk, SonarQube) — investigates and opens fix PRs','Weekly codebase sweep: secret detection, permission review, CVE scan','Files Jira security tickets with CVSS severity, affected files, and remediation steps','Posts weekly security posture summary to the security channel — trend over time'],playbookSample:'# !security-review\nFor any PR touching src/auth/, src/payments/, src/data/:\n1. Check for injection vulnerabilities (SQL, command, LDAP)\n2. Review token/secret handling — no hardcoded values\n3. Verify input validation on all public endpoints\n4. Check for insecure direct object references\n5. Review error messages — no stack traces in responses\n6. Post findings as GitHub review comments with severity\n7. File Jira security ticket for MEDIUM or above'}];

